{
  "video_id": "WvfydcUeXls",
  "title": "A love letter to realism in a time of grief | Mark Pollock and Simone George",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13802.0,
      "end_time": 16961.0,
      "text": "Simone George: I met Mark when he was just blind."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17389.0,
      "end_time": 19389.0,
      "text": "I had returned home to live in Dublin"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19413.0,
      "end_time": 22815.0,
      "text": "after the odyssey that was my 20s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22839.0,
      "end_time": 27156.0,
      "text": "educating my interest in human rights and equality in university,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 27180.0,
      "end_time": 30380.0,
      "text": "traveling the world, like my nomad grandmother."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 30831.0,
      "end_time": 34513.0,
      "text": "And during a two-year stint working in Madrid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 34538.0,
      "end_time": 38282.0,
      "text": "dancing many nights till morning in salsa clubs."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 39903.0,
      "end_time": 42887.0,
      "text": "When I met Mark, he asked me to teach him to dance."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 43188.0,
      "end_time": 44338.0,
      "text": "And I did."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 45515.0,
      "end_time": 48371.0,
      "text": "They were wonderful times, long nights talking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 48395.0,
      "end_time": 51728.0,
      "text": "becoming friends and eventually falling for each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 53203.0,
      "end_time": 55918.0,
      "text": "Mark had lost his sight when he was 22,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 55942.0,
      "end_time": 60744.0,
      "text": "and the man that I met eight years later was rebuilding his identity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 60768.0,
      "end_time": 64717.0,
      "text": "the cornerstone of which was this incredible spirit"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 64741.0,
      "end_time": 69416.0,
      "text": "that had taken him to the Gobi Desert, where he ran six marathons in seven days."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 69918.0,
      "end_time": 74113.0,
      "text": "And to marathons at the North Pole, and from Everest Base Camp."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 75312.0,
      "end_time": 79180.0,
      "text": "When I asked him what had led to this high-octane life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 79430.0,
      "end_time": 81161.0,
      "text": "he quoted Nietzsche:"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 81185.0,
      "end_time": 85552.0,
      "text": "\"He, who has a Why to live, can bear with almost any How.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 87900.0,
      "end_time": 90200.0,
      "text": "He had come across the quote in a really beautiful book"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 90260.0,
      "end_time": 93609.0,
      "text": "called \"Man&#39;s Search for Meaning,\" by Viktor Frankl,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 93633.0,
      "end_time": 95839.0,
      "text": "a neurologist and psychiatrist"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 95863.0,
      "end_time": 99630.0,
      "text": "who survived years in a Nazi concentration camp."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 99561.0,
      "end_time": 103792.0,
      "text": "Frankl used this Nietzsche quote to explain to us"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 103816.0,
      "end_time": 107180.0,
      "text": "that when we can no longer change our circumstances,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 107204.0,
      "end_time": 110204.0,
      "text": "we are challenged to change ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 112188.0,
      "end_time": 115403.0,
      "text": "Mark Pollock: Eventually, I did rebuild my identity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 115427.0,
      "end_time": 118482.0,
      "text": "and the Why for me was about competing again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 118506.0,
      "end_time": 122125.0,
      "text": "because pursuing success and risking failure"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 122149.0,
      "end_time": 125850.0,
      "text": "was simply how I felt normal."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 125957.0,
      "end_time": 128369.0,
      "text": "And I finished the rebuild"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 128393.0,
      "end_time": 131327.0,
      "text": "on the 10th anniversary of losing my sight."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 131861.0,
      "end_time": 135887.0,
      "text": "I took part in a 43-day expedition race"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 135911.0,
      "end_time": 140282.0,
      "text": "in the coldest, most remote, most challenging place on earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 140783.0,
      "end_time": 142841.0,
      "text": "It was the first race to the South Pole"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 142866.0,
      "end_time": 149159.0,
      "text": "since Shackleton, Scott and Amundsen set foot in Antarctica, 100 years before."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 150180.0,
      "end_time": 152963.0,
      "text": "And putting the demons of blindness behind me"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 152987.0,
      "end_time": 155769.0,
      "text": "with every step towards the pole,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 155794.0,
      "end_time": 159778.0,
      "text": "it offered me a long-lasting sense of contentment."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 161736.0,
      "end_time": 164974.0,
      "text": "As it turned out, I would need that in reserve,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 164998.0,
      "end_time": 169101.0,
      "text": "because one year after my return,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 169125.0,
      "end_time": 172157.0,
      "text": "in, arguably, the safest place on earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 172181.0,
      "end_time": 175513.0,
      "text": "a bedroom at a friend&#39;s house,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 175537.0,
      "end_time": 181323.0,
      "text": "I fell from a third-story window onto the concrete below."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 182164.0,
      "end_time": 183702.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know how it happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 184133.0,
      "end_time": 186688.0,
      "text": "I think I must have got up to go to the bathroom."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 187500.0,
      "end_time": 192442.0,
      "text": "And because I&#39;m blind, I used to run my hand along the wall"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 192466.0,
      "end_time": 193616.0,
      "text": "to find my way."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 194704.0,
      "end_time": 200502.0,
      "text": "That night, my hand found an open space where the closed window should have been."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 201252.0,
      "end_time": 202719.0,
      "text": "And I cartwheeled out."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 203657.0,
      "end_time": 206290.0,
      "text": "My friends who found me thought I was dead."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 206530.0,
      "end_time": 209903.0,
      "text": "When I got to hospital, the doctors thought I was going to die,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 209927.0,
      "end_time": 212261.0,
      "text": "and when I realized what was happening to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 212285.0,
      "end_time": 215714.0,
      "text": "I thought that dying might have been ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 217157.0,
      "end_time": 219498.0,
      "text": "might have been the best outcome."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 220125.0,
      "end_time": 222624.0,
      "text": "And lying in intensive care,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 222648.0,
      "end_time": 227458.0,
      "text": "facing the prospect of being blind and paralyzed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 227482.0,
      "end_time": 232202.0,
      "text": "high on morphine, I was trying to make sense of what was going on."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 233139.0,
      "end_time": 235902.0,
      "text": "And one night, lying flat on my back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 235926.0,
      "end_time": 242518.0,
      "text": "I felt for my phone to write a blog,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 242543.0,
      "end_time": 244903.0,
      "text": "trying to explain how I should respond."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 244927.0,
      "end_time": 248839.0,
      "text": "It was called \"Optimist, Realist or Something Else?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 248863.0,
      "end_time": 252220.0,
      "text": "and it drew on the experiences of Admiral Stockdale,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 252460.0,
      "end_time": 254588.0,
      "text": "who was a POW in the Vietnam war."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 256910.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260996.00000000003,
      "text": "He was incarcerated, tortured, for over seven years."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 261209.99999999997,
      "end_time": 264790.0,
      "text": "His circumstances were bleak, but he survived."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 265513.0,
      "end_time": 268536.0,
      "text": "The ones who didn&#39;t survive were the optimists."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 269840.0,
      "end_time": 271600.0,
      "text": "They said, \"We&#39;ll be out by Christmas,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 271840.0,
      "end_time": 273892.0,
      "text": "and Christmas would come and Christmas would go,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 273916.0,
      "end_time": 276141.0,
      "text": "and then it would be Christmas again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 276165.0,
      "end_time": 281570.0,
      "text": "and when they didn&#39;t get out, they became disappointed, demoralized"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 281594.0,
      "end_time": 284569.0,
      "text": "and many of them died in their cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 286323.0,
      "end_time": 289132.0,
      "text": "Stockdale was a realist."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 289474.0,
      "end_time": 292780.0,
      "text": "He was inspired by the stoic philosophers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 292804.0,
      "end_time": 299260.0,
      "text": "and he confronted the brutal facts of his circumstances"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 299284.0,
      "end_time": 303369.0,
      "text": "while maintaining a faith that he would prevail in the end."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 304530.0,
      "end_time": 308410.0,
      "text": "And in that blog, I was trying to apply his thinking as a realist"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 308650.0,
      "end_time": 310665.0,
      "text": "to my increasingly bleak circumstances."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 311609.0,
      "end_time": 315530.0,
      "text": "During the many months of heart infections and kidney infections"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 315770.0,
      "end_time": 319147.0,
      "text": "after my fall, at the very edge of survival,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 320172.0,
      "end_time": 324386.0,
      "text": "Simone and I faced the fundamental question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 325891.0,
      "end_time": 330804.0,
      "text": "How do you resolve the tension between acceptance and hope?"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 330828.0,
      "end_time": 333866.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s that that we want to explore with you now."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 335228.0,
      "end_time": 338395.0,
      "text": "SG: After I got the call, I caught the first flight to England"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 338419.0,
      "end_time": 342228.0,
      "text": "and arrived into the brightly lit intensive care ward,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 342252.0,
      "end_time": 345537.0,
      "text": "where Mark was lying naked, just under a sheet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 345561.0,
      "end_time": 349447.0,
      "text": "connected to machines that were monitoring if he would live."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 350850.0,
      "end_time": 352623.0,
      "text": "I said, \"I&#39;m here, Mark.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 353180.0,
      "end_time": 357453.0,
      "text": "And he cried tears he seemed to have saved just for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 358641.0,
      "end_time": 363440.0,
      "text": "I wanted to gather him in my arms, but I couldn&#39;t move him,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 363680.0,
      "end_time": 367163.0,
      "text": "and so I kissed him the way you kiss a newborn baby,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 367187.0,
      "end_time": 369178.0,
      "text": "terrified of their fragility."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 370673.0,
      "end_time": 374839.0,
      "text": "Later that afternoon, when the bad news had been laid out for us --"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 374863.0,
      "end_time": 379156.0,
      "text": "fractured skull, bleeds on his brain, a possible torn aorta"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 379180.0,
      "end_time": 385188.0,
      "text": "and a spine broken in two places, no movement or feeling below his waist --"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 385212.0,
      "end_time": 388180.0,
      "text": "Mark said to me, \"Come here."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 389109.0,
      "end_time": 393702.0,
      "text": "You need to get yourself as far away from this as possible.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 395577.0,
      "end_time": 398276.0,
      "text": "As I tried to process what he was saying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 398300.0,
      "end_time": 401815.0,
      "text": "I was thinking, \"What the hell is wrong with you?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 401839.0,
      "end_time": 403553.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 403577.0,
      "end_time": 405171.0,
      "text": "\"We can&#39;t do this now.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 405990.0,
      "end_time": 409140.0,
      "text": "So I asked him, \"Are you breaking up with me?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 409380.0,
      "end_time": 412554.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 412578.0,
      "end_time": 417236.0,
      "text": "And he said, \"Look, you signed up for the blindness, but not this.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 418477.0,
      "end_time": 421318.0,
      "text": "And I answered, \"We don&#39;t even know what this is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 421342.0,
      "end_time": 424800.0,
      "text": "but what I do know is what I can&#39;t handle right now"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 424320.0,
      "end_time": 427510.0,
      "text": "is a breakup while someone I love is in intensive care.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 427760.0,
      "end_time": 429439.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 429463.0,
      "end_time": 433488.0,
      "text": "So I called on my negotiation skills and suggested we make a deal."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 434178.0,
      "end_time": 437971.0,
      "text": "I said, \"I will stay with you as long as you need me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 437995.0,
      "end_time": 440610.0,
      "text": "as long as your back needs me."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 440850.0,
      "end_time": 444162.0,
      "text": "And when you no longer need me, then we talk about our relationship.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 444577.0,
      "end_time": 448315.0,
      "text": "Like a contract with the possibility to renew in six months."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 448339.0,
      "end_time": 450201.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 451458.0,
      "end_time": 453775.0,
      "text": "He agreed and I stayed."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 454339.0,
      "end_time": 458855.0,
      "text": "In fact, I refused to go home even to pack a bag, I slept by his bed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 458879.0,
      "end_time": 461363.0,
      "text": "when he could eat, I made all his food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 461387.0,
      "end_time": 466890.0,
      "text": "and we cried, one or other or both of us together, every day."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 467482.0,
      "end_time": 470895.0,
      "text": "I made all the complicated decisions with the doctors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 470919.0,
      "end_time": 477847.0,
      "text": "I climbed right into that raging river over rapids that was sweeping Mark along."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 480371.0,
      "end_time": 484744.0,
      "text": "And at the first bend in that river, Mark&#39;s surgeon told us"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 484768.0,
      "end_time": 488886.0,
      "text": "what movement and feeling he doesn&#39;t get back in the first 12 weeks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 488911.0,
      "end_time": 491355.0,
      "text": "he&#39;s unlikely to get back at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 493460.0,
      "end_time": 496108.0,
      "text": "So, sitting by his bed, I began to research why,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 496132.0,
      "end_time": 499460.0,
      "text": "after this period they call spinal shock,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 499700.0,
      "end_time": 503960.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s no recovery, there&#39;s no therapy, there&#39;s no cure, there&#39;s no hope."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 505111.0,
      "end_time": 509498.0,
      "text": "And the internet became this portal to a magical other world."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 509523.0,
      "end_time": 511698.0,
      "text": "I emailed scientists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 511722.0,
      "end_time": 513227.0,
      "text": "and they broke through paywalls"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 513251.0,
      "end_time": 517183.0,
      "text": "and sent me their medical journal and science journal articles directly."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 517568.0,
      "end_time": 520967.0,
      "text": "I read everything that \"Superman\" actor Christopher Reeve had achieved,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 520991.0,
      "end_time": 522355.0,
      "text": "after a fall from a horse"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 522379.0,
      "end_time": 525979.0,
      "text": "left him paralyzed from the neck down and ventilated."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 526553.0,
      "end_time": 529860.0,
      "text": "Christopher had broken this 12-week spell;"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 529110.0,
      "end_time": 533267.0,
      "text": "he had regained some movement and feeling years after his accident."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 534489.0,
      "end_time": 538289.0,
      "text": "He dreamed of a world of empty wheelchairs."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 539117.0,
      "end_time": 543829.0,
      "text": "And Christopher and the scientists he worked with fueled us with hope."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 546363.0,
      "end_time": 548499.0,
      "text": "MP: You see, spinal cord injury"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 548523.0,
      "end_time": 552323.0,
      "text": "strikes at the very heart of what it means to be human."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 552347.0,
      "end_time": 557294.0,
      "text": "And it had turned me from my upright, standing, running form,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 557318.0,
      "end_time": 560818.0,
      "text": "into a seated compromise of myself."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 561128.0,
      "end_time": 564528.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s not just the lack of feeling and movement."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 564919.0,
      "end_time": 568370.0,
      "text": "Paralysis also interferes with the body&#39;s internal systems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 568610.0,
      "end_time": 570461.0,
      "text": "which are designed to keep us alive."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 571204.0,
      "end_time": 576275.0,
      "text": "Multiple infections, nerve pain, spasms, shortened life spans are common."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 576656.0,
      "end_time": 579799.0,
      "text": "And these are the things that exhaust even the most determined"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 579823.0,
      "end_time": 582915.0,
      "text": "of the 60 million people around the world who are paralyzed."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 585710.0,
      "end_time": 588155.0,
      "text": "Over 16 months in hospital,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 588179.0,
      "end_time": 591180.0,
      "text": "Simone and I were presented with the expert view"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 591204.0,
      "end_time": 594933.0,
      "text": "that hoping for a cure had proven to be psychologically damaging."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 595434.0,
      "end_time": 599172.0,
      "text": "It was like the formal medical system was canceling hope"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 599196.0,
      "end_time": 602145.0,
      "text": "in favor of acceptance alone."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 602815.0,
      "end_time": 607664.0,
      "text": "But canceling hope ran contrary to everything that we believed in."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 609500.0,
      "end_time": 612583.0,
      "text": "Yes, up to this point in history,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 612607.0,
      "end_time": 615420.0,
      "text": "it had proven to be impossible to find a cure for paralysis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 615445.0,
      "end_time": 620141.0,
      "text": "but history is filled with the kinds of the impossible made possible"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 620165.0,
      "end_time": 621698.0,
      "text": "through human endeavor."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 622600.0,
      "end_time": 625140.0,
      "text": "The kind of human endeavor that took explorers to the South Pole"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 625164.0,
      "end_time": 627188.0,
      "text": "at the start of the last century."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 627212.0,
      "end_time": 629172.0,
      "text": "And the kind of human endeavor"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 629196.0,
      "end_time": 633863.0,
      "text": "that will take adventurers to Mars in the early part of this century."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 634641.0,
      "end_time": 636704.0,
      "text": "So we started asking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 636728.0,
      "end_time": 641282.0,
      "text": "\"Why can&#39;t that same human endeavor cure paralysis in our lifetime?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 642528.0,
      "end_time": 645726.0,
      "text": "SG: Well, we really believed that it can."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 645750.0,
      "end_time": 647500.0,
      "text": "My research taught us"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 647290.0,
      "end_time": 652331.0,
      "text": "that we needed to remind Mark&#39;s damaged and dormant spinal cord"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 652355.0,
      "end_time": 654632.0,
      "text": "of its upright, standing, running form,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 654656.0,
      "end_time": 659258.0,
      "text": "and we found San Francisco-based engineers at Ekso Bionics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 659283.0,
      "end_time": 663833.0,
      "text": "who created this robotic exoskeleton that would allow Mark to stand and walk"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 663857.0,
      "end_time": 666990.0,
      "text": "in the lab that we started to build in Dublin."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 667911.0,
      "end_time": 671806.0,
      "text": "Mark became the first person to personally own an exo,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 671831.0,
      "end_time": 676431.0,
      "text": "and since then, he and the robot have walked over one million steps."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 677395.0,
      "end_time": 682822.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 682846.0,
      "end_time": 686163.0,
      "text": "It was bit of an early celebration, because actually it wasn&#39;t enough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 686187.0,
      "end_time": 688983.0,
      "text": "the robot was doing all of the work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 689700.0,
      "end_time": 691178.0,
      "text": "so we needed to plug Mark in."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 691934.0,
      "end_time": 694632.0,
      "text": "So we connected the San Francisco engineers"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 694657.0,
      "end_time": 699641.0,
      "text": "with a true visionary in UCLA, Dr. Reggie Edgerton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 699665.0,
      "end_time": 701506.0,
      "text": "the most beautiful man"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 701530.0,
      "end_time": 706820.0,
      "text": "and his team&#39;s life work had resulted in a scientific breakthrough."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 706704.0,
      "end_time": 709839.0,
      "text": "Using electrical stimulation of the spinal cord,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 709864.0,
      "end_time": 712683.0,
      "text": "a number of subjects have been able to stand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 712707.0,
      "end_time": 715888.0,
      "text": "and because of that, regain some movement and feeling"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 715912.0,
      "end_time": 717515.0,
      "text": "and most importantly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 717539.0,
      "end_time": 720846.0,
      "text": "to regain some of the body&#39;s internal functions"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 720870.0,
      "end_time": 725751.0,
      "text": "that are designed to keep us alive and to make that life a pleasure."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 726903.0,
      "end_time": 729863.0,
      "text": "Electrical stimulation of the spinal cord,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 729887.0,
      "end_time": 734986.0,
      "text": "we think, is the first meaningful therapy ever for paralyzed people."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 736692.0,
      "end_time": 738728.0,
      "text": "Now, of course, the San Francisco engineers"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 738752.0,
      "end_time": 740607.0,
      "text": "and the scientists in UCLA"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 740631.0,
      "end_time": 743400.0,
      "text": "knew about each other, knew about each other&#39;s work."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 743424.0,
      "end_time": 745395.0,
      "text": "But as so often happens"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 745419.0,
      "end_time": 752331.0,
      "text": "when we&#39;re busy creating groundbreaking scientific research,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 752355.0,
      "end_time": 754688.0,
      "text": "they hadn&#39;t quite yet got together."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 755442.0,
      "end_time": 757664.0,
      "text": "That seemed to be our job now."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 758609.0,
      "end_time": 761522.0,
      "text": "So we created our first collaboration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 761546.0,
      "end_time": 763150.0,
      "text": "and the moment when we combined"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 763174.0,
      "end_time": 766690.0,
      "text": "the electrical stimulation of Mark&#39;s spinal cord,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 766930.0,
      "end_time": 768617.0,
      "text": "as he walked in his robotic exoskeleton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 768641.0,
      "end_time": 773290.0,
      "text": "was like that moment when Iron Man plugs the mini arc reactor into his chest"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 773530.0,
      "end_time": 777506.0,
      "text": "and suddenly he and his suit become something else altogether."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 779466.0,
      "end_time": 784950.0,
      "text": "MP: Simone, my robot and I moved into the lab at UCLA for three months."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 784974.0,
      "end_time": 787395.0,
      "text": "And every day, Reggie and his team"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 787419.0,
      "end_time": 790783.0,
      "text": "put electrodes onto the skin on my lower back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 790807.0,
      "end_time": 795283.0,
      "text": "pushed electricity into my spinal cord to excite my nervous system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 795307.0,
      "end_time": 798500.0,
      "text": "as I walked in my exo."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 798538.0,
      "end_time": 800839.0,
      "text": "And for the first time since I was paralyzed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 800863.0,
      "end_time": 803640.0,
      "text": "I could feel my legs underneath me."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 804347.0,
      "end_time": 805515.0,
      "text": "Not normally --"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 805539.0,
      "end_time": 807425.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 807450.0,
      "end_time": 808693.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 808718.0,
      "end_time": 810161.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 810553.0,
      "end_time": 813752.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t a normal feeling, but with the stimulator turned on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 813776.0,
      "end_time": 817521.0,
      "text": "upright in my exo, my legs felt substantial."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 817546.0,
      "end_time": 823149.0,
      "text": "I could feel the meat of my muscles on the bones of my legs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 823173.0,
      "end_time": 826339.0,
      "text": "and as I walked, because of the stimulation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 826363.0,
      "end_time": 829863.0,
      "text": "I was able to voluntarily move my paralyzed legs."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 829887.0,
      "end_time": 834758.0,
      "text": "And as I did more, the robot intelligently did less."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 834783.0,
      "end_time": 838188.0,
      "text": "My heart rate got a normal running, training zone"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 838212.0,
      "end_time": 840982.0,
      "text": "of 140 to 160 beats per minute,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 841600.0,
      "end_time": 845752.0,
      "text": "and my muscles, which had almost entirely disappeared,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 845776.0,
      "end_time": 847175.0,
      "text": "started to come back."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 847514.0,
      "end_time": 851117.0,
      "text": "And during some standard testing throughout the process,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 851141.0,
      "end_time": 852887.0,
      "text": "flat on my back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 852911.0,
      "end_time": 856926.0,
      "text": "twelve weeks, six months and three whole years"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 856951.0,
      "end_time": 860266.0,
      "text": "after I fell out that window and became paralyzed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 860290.0,
      "end_time": 864450.0,
      "text": "the scientists turned the stimulator on"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 864690.0,
      "end_time": 867990.0,
      "text": "and I pulled my knee to my chest."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 868704.0,
      "end_time": 871989.0,
      "text": "(Video) Man: OK, start, go, go, go, go, go."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 872140.0,
      "end_time": 873164.0,
      "text": "Good, good, good."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 873188.0,
      "end_time": 877164.0,
      "text": "SG: Yeah, yeah, go on, Mark, go on, go, go, go, go, go, wow!"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 877188.0,
      "end_time": 878339.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 878363.0,
      "end_time": 879577.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 880339.0,
      "end_time": 881490.0,
      "text": "SG: Well done!"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 881514.0,
      "end_time": 884333.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 885183.0,
      "end_time": 887755.0,
      "text": "MP: Do you know, this week, I&#39;ve been saying to Simone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 887779.0,
      "end_time": 890390.0,
      "text": "if we could forget about the paralysis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 890414.0,
      "end_time": 893434.0,
      "text": "you know, the last few years have been incredibly exciting."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 893458.0,
      "end_time": 896156.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 896180.0,
      "end_time": 901299.0,
      "text": "Now, the problem is, we can&#39;t quite forget about the paralysis just yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 901323.0,
      "end_time": 902879.0,
      "text": "And clearly, we&#39;re not finished,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 902903.0,
      "end_time": 905823.0,
      "text": "because when we left that pilot study and went back to Dublin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 905847.0,
      "end_time": 907569.0,
      "text": "I rolled home in my wheelchair"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 907593.0,
      "end_time": 910277.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m still paralyzed and I&#39;m still blind"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 910302.0,
      "end_time": 913149.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re primarily focusing on the paralysis at the moment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 913173.0,
      "end_time": 914681.0,
      "text": "but being at this conference,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 914705.0,
      "end_time": 917823.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re kind of interested if anyone does have a cure for blindness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 917847.0,
      "end_time": 919448.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ll take that as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 919472.0,
      "end_time": 921569.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 921594.0,
      "end_time": 927810.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 927569.0,
      "end_time": 930673.0,
      "text": "But if you remember the blog that I mentioned,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 930697.0,
      "end_time": 933347.0,
      "text": "it posed a question of how we should respond,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 933371.0,
      "end_time": 936210.0,
      "text": "optimist, realist or something else?"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 936450.0,
      "end_time": 940545.0,
      "text": "And I think we have come to understand that the optimists rely on hope alone"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 940569.0,
      "end_time": 943276.0,
      "text": "and they risk being disappointed and demoralized."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 944479.0,
      "end_time": 946810.0,
      "text": "The realists, on the other hand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 948129.0,
      "end_time": 953649.0,
      "text": "they accept the brutal facts and they keep hope alive, as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 954340.0,
      "end_time": 959964.0,
      "text": "The realists have managed to resolve the tension between acceptance and hope"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 959988.0,
      "end_time": 962352.0,
      "text": "by running them in parallel."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 962376.0,
      "end_time": 964757.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s what Simone and I have been trying to do"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 964782.0,
      "end_time": 966259.0,
      "text": "over the last number of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 966283.0,
      "end_time": 968718.0,
      "text": "Look, I accept the wheelchair --"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 968742.0,
      "end_time": 971670.0,
      "text": "I mean, it&#39;s almost impossible not to."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 971910.0,
      "end_time": 974430.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;re sad, sometimes, for what we&#39;ve lost."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 974623.0,
      "end_time": 980200.0,
      "text": "I accept that I, and other wheelchair users, can and do live fulfilling lives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 980260.0,
      "end_time": 983510.0,
      "text": "despite the nerve pain and the spasms and the infections"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 983534.0,
      "end_time": 985201.0,
      "text": "and the shortened life spans."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 985765.0,
      "end_time": 987982.0,
      "text": "And I accept that it is way more difficult"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 988600.0,
      "end_time": 990593.0,
      "text": "for people who are paralyzed from the neck down."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 990617.0,
      "end_time": 993487.0,
      "text": "For those who rely on ventilators to breathe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 993511.0,
      "end_time": 998257.0,
      "text": "and for those who don&#39;t have access to adequate, free health care."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 998967.0,
      "end_time": 1004117.0,
      "text": "So, that is why we also hope for another life."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 1004470.0,
      "end_time": 1008272.0,
      "text": "A life where we have created a cure through collaboration."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 1008640.0,
      "end_time": 1013292.0,
      "text": "A cure that we are actively working to release from university labs"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 1013310.0,
      "end_time": 1014595.0,
      "text": "around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 1014620.0,
      "end_time": 1017706.0,
      "text": "and share with everyone who needs it."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 1019990.0,
      "end_time": 1022887.0,
      "text": "SG: I met Mark when he was just blind."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 1024170.0000000001,
      "end_time": 1027360.0000000001,
      "text": "He asked me to teach him to dance, and I did."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 1028119.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1029841.9999999999,
      "text": "One night, after dance classes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 1029869.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1032327.9999999999,
      "text": "I turned to say goodnight to him at his front door,"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 1032349.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1035206.9999999999,
      "text": "and to his gorgeous guide dog, Larry."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 1035750.0,
      "end_time": 1039598.0,
      "text": "I realized, that in switching all the lights off in the apartment"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 1039849.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1040251.9999999999,
      "text": "before I left,"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 1040280.0,
      "end_time": 1042198.0,
      "text": "that I was leaving him in the dark."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 1043490.0,
      "end_time": 1049647.0,
      "text": "I burst into uncontrollable tears and tried to hide it, but he knew."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 1050280.0,
      "end_time": 1053160.0,
      "text": "And he hugged me and said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 1053190.0,
      "end_time": 1054655.0,
      "text": "\"Ah, poor Simone."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 1055460.0,
      "end_time": 1057877.0,
      "text": "You&#39;re back in 1998, when I went blind."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 1059580.0,
      "end_time": 1062929.0,
      "text": "Don&#39;t worry, it turns out OK in the end.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 1064650.0,
      "end_time": 1069976.0,
      "text": "Acceptance is knowing that grief is a raging river."
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 1071190.0,
      "end_time": 1073533.0,
      "text": "And you have to get into it."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 1073650.0,
      "end_time": 1077316.0,
      "text": "Because when you do, it carries you to the next place."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 1078130.0,
      "end_time": 1080820.0,
      "text": "It eventually takes you to open land,"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 1080850.0,
      "end_time": 1084366.0,
      "text": "somewhere where it will turn out OK in the end."
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 1086960.0,
      "end_time": 1089627.0,
      "text": "And it truly has been a love story,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 1089650.0,
      "end_time": 1095428.0,
      "text": "an expansive, abundant, deeply satisfying kind of love"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 1095450.0,
      "end_time": 1100567.0,
      "text": "for our fellow humans and everyone in this act of creation."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 1102330.0,
      "end_time": 1104353.0,
      "text": "Science is love."
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 1105150.0,
      "end_time": 1106753.0,
      "text": "Everyone we&#39;ve met in this field"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 1106780.0,
      "end_time": 1110829.0,
      "text": "just wants to get their work from the bench and into people&#39;s lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 1111550.0,
      "end_time": 1114283.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s our job to help them to do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 1115380.0,
      "end_time": 1119624.0,
      "text": "Because when we do, we and everyone with us"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 1119650.0,
      "end_time": 1121537.0,
      "text": "in this act of creation"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 1121560.0,
      "end_time": 1123807.0,
      "text": "will be able to say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 1123830.0,
      "end_time": 1125504.0,
      "text": "\"We did it."
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 1125530.0,
      "end_time": 1126863.0,
      "text": "And then we danced.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 1129240.0,
      "end_time": 1135765.0,
      "text": "(Video) (Music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 1136800.0,
      "end_time": 1137950.0,
      "text": "SG: Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 1138820.0,
      "end_time": 1143729.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 1143760.0,
      "end_time": 1144918.0,
      "text": "MP: Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 1144940.0,
      "end_time": 1151849.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 1153290.0,
      "end_time": 1154440.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 1154460.0,
      "end_time": 1161395.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}